Currently, we are looking for a homestay for two Chinese students who are going to Parsons School of Design to take short-term program from 8/5 - 8/18. The host parents serve as responsible adults in place of the parent(s) for the international student. We expect the home near public transportation and students can take bus/train that directly bring them to Columbia University. 

1. Provide a clean, orderly, pleasant and safe living environment for the international student that we host; 
2. Provide the international student with adequate sleeping quarters, suitable furnishings (including a desk); 
3. Provide the international student with reasonable access and use of bathroom, laundry facilities and other the common areas of our home (including internet access available for the international student), as well as necessary household items (e.g., linens, towels, blankets, pillow etc.);
4. Provide an environment conducive to study and completion of homework and demonstrate a supportive interest in international student's progress at School; 
5. Involve the international student in activities and outings and generally make them feel a part of our family, and we will encourage and support the student to participate in social and recreational activities outside our immediate family and the school environment; 
6. Provide a variety of nutritional, well-balanced meals on a regular basis, including at least two meals per day during weekends and school holidays, and breakfasts and dinners on school days. (with the understanding that lunch is not included, the international student may purchase at school is in session); 

If you are interested, please feel free to contact me. Thank you


